        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 7:54PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 753 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Tionesta, or 30 miles north of Bieber, moving
northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tionesta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
